Access or assign mass at age

Source: R/mass.R
mass.Rd

This function can be used to access or assign the biomass at age in an lhm object.

Assignment can be of a list or numeric vector. When a list is assigned it should provide the \(a\) and \(b\) parameters of the function: $$Mass = a * Length ^ b.$$

Uncertainty accross iterations in the lhm object can be included by providing either an overall coefficient of variation (cv) or a cv for each of the parameters. Overall uncertainty is assumed to be log-normal with \(\sigma = \sqrt{ln(1+cv^2)}\). Parameter uncertainty is assumed to be normal with \(\sigma = \mu * cv\).

When assigning a numeric vector it is assumed that each replicate is identical.

Usage

mass(object, ...)

# S4 method for class 'lhm'
mass(object)

mass(object) <- value

# S4 method for class 'lhm,list'
mass(object) <- value

# S4 method for class 'lhm,numeric'
mass(object) <- value

Arguments

object

a lhm object

...

arguments to generic function

value

either a named list or numeric vector

numeric

a vector of length equal to the maximum age

list

a list object containing the components mu and cv

mu

a list containing the parameters a and b representing their mean values

cv

optional single numeric value or a list containing parameters a and b representing their coefficients of variation

Value

Accessor function returns a matrix of mass at age across iterations. Assignment function populates the matrix across iterations.
